  "text": "4.4. The Greenland Ice Sheet as a \"Hot Spot\" of Phosphorus Denudation 4.4.1. SRP Denudation Our results suggest that the GrIS is among the most efficient regions of P weathering and export in the world. Dissolved P yields are among the highest observed in literature (Table 2) . These rates are elevated compared to those reported in other glacial catchments, apart from [CITATION_1] (Table 4) , where SRP yields >30 kg km À2 yr À1 were recorded at two North American glaciated watersheds.",
