    "53996278": {
      "title": "Riverine organic matter and nutrients in southeast Alaska affected by glacial coverage",
      "abstract": "Dissolved organic matter and nutrients from high-latitude coastal watersheds stimulate microbial activity and primary productivity in near-shore ecosystems. A survey of southeast Alaskan watersheds suggests that the extent of glacial coverage may control the release of these nutrients to rivers and ultimately the oceans."
